The boundary conditions may be:
- a FOURIER-ROBIN condition 
(normal flux:- conduc d temperature/dn = ECHANGE (temperature-exterior temperature))
  input the heat transfer coefficient ECHANGE(1)
	and the heat SOURCE(2) = ECHANGE * exterior fluid temperature

- a NEUMANN condition (conduc d temperature/dn = SOURCE)
  input SOURCE(2)= heat normal flux

- a DIRICHLET condition (temperature = CONTACT)
  input the CONTACT(3) equal to the imposed temperature for every node
